@notice Initiate the account with the address of the ERC725Account contract and sets LSP6KeyManager InterfaceId
 @param _account The address of the ER725Account to control

devdoc.author: Fabian Vogelsteller <frozeman>, Jean Cavallera (CJ42), Yamen Merhi (YamenMerhi)
devdoc.details: all the permissions can be set on the ERC725 Account using `setData(...)` with the keys constants below

NoPermissionsSet(address).details: revert when address `from` does not have any permissions set on the account linked to this Key Manager

params.from: the address that does not have permissions

NotAllowedAddress(address,address).details: address `from` is not authorised to interact with `disallowedAddress` via account

params.disallowedAddress: address that `from` is not authorised to call

NotAllowedERC725YKey(address,bytes32).details: address `from` is not authorised to set the key `disallowedKey` on the account

params.disallowedKey: a bytes32 key that `from` is not authorised to set on the ERC725Y storage

NotAllowedFunction(address,bytes4).details: address `from` is not authorised to run `disallowedFunction` via account

params.disallowedFunction: bytes4 function selector that `from` is not authorised to run

params._account: The address of the ER725Account to control

execute(bytes).details: the ERC725Account will return some data on successful call, or revert on failure

params._calldata: the payload to execute. Obtained in web3 via encodeABI()

returns._0: result_ the data being returned by the ERC725 Account

executeRelayCall(bytes,uint256,bytes).details: allows anybody to execute given they have a signed message from an executor

params._nonce: the address' nonce (in a specific `_channel`), obtained via `getNonce(...)`. Used to prevent replay attack

returns._0: result_ the data being returned by the ERC725 Account

getNonce(address,uint256).details: use channel ID = 0 for sequential nonces, any other number for out-of-order execution (= execution in parallel)

isValidSignature(bytes32,bytes).details: Should return whether the signature provided is valid for the provided data

params.hash: Hash of the data to be signed

devdoc.title: Implementation of a contract acting as a controller of an ERC725 Account, using permissions stored in the ERC725Y storage

constructor.notice: Initiate the account with the address of the ERC725Account contract and sets LSP6KeyManager InterfaceId

execute(bytes).notice: execute the following payload on the ERC725Account: `_calldata`

getNonce(address,uint256).notice: get latest nonce for `_from` for channel ID: `_channel`

target().notice: returns the address of the account linked to this KeyManager
